		"description": "<p>This fine gray dust is usually found in a vial and appears to be <em>dust of disappearance</em>, even when magic is used to <em>identify</em> it. Each vial contains enough for a single use. </p><p>You can use an action to throw the dust into the air. You and creatures within 30 feet of you that breathe make a DC 15 Constitution saving throw or become wracked with violent coughing and sneezing, becoming incapacitated and beginning to suffocate. While conscious, a creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effects on a success. A <em>lesser restoration</em> spell also ends the effects.</p>",
